Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharp turn. Clay fine buff. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Production date: 179 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes (2015) 142.)
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (?)
Curator's comments: Name Ainesidamos. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0041.15.
